---
import Layout from '../layouts/main.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Terms of Service - Public Code US"
	description="Terms of service for the Public Code US petition website."
	currentPage="/terms"
>
	<section class="bg-am-light border-b-4 border-am-dark py-20">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
			<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-am-dark mb-12">Terms of Service</h1>

			<div class="space-y-8">
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-am-dark mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
					<p class="font-bold text-am-dark leading-relaxed">
						By accessing and using this website, you accept and agree to be bound by the terms and provision of this agreement. If you do not agree to abide by the above, please do not use this service.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="border-4 border-am-dark bg-am-blue p-6">
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-am-dark mb-4">2. Use License</h2>
					<p class="font-bold text-am-dark mb-4">Permission is granted to temporarily download one copy of the materials (information or software) on Public Code US's website for personal, non-commercial transitory viewing only. This is the grant of a license, not a transfer of title, and under this license you may not:</p>
					<ul class="font-bold text-am-dark space-y-2">
						<li>• Modify or copy the materials</li>
						<li>• Use the materials for any commercial purpose or for any public display</li>
						<li>• Attempt to modify, translate, adapt, decompile, reverse engineer, disassemble, or otherwise derive source code</li>
						<li>• Remove any copyright or other proprietary notations from the materials</li>
						<li>• Transfer the materials to another person or "mirror" the materials on any other server</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-am-dark mb-4">3. Petition Signature Agreement</h2>
					<p class="font-bold text-am-dark mb-4">By signing the petition, you:</p>
					<ul class="font-bold text-am-dark space-y-2">
						<li>✓ Certify that you are a registered voter in the United States</li>
						<li>✓ Are providing truthful and accurate information</li>
						<li>✓ Authorize your signature to be used for ballot initiative qualification</li>
						<li>✓ Understand your signature may be shared with state election authorities as required by law</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="border-4 border-am-dark bg-am-red text-am-light p-6">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Disclaimer</h2>
					<p class="font-bold mb-4">
						The materials on Public Code US's website are provided on an "as-is" basis. Public Code US makes no warranties, expressed or implied, and hereby disclaims and negates all other warranties including, without limitation, implied warranties or conditions of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement of intellectual property or other violation of rights.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-am-dark mb-4">5. Limitations</h2>
					<p class="font-bold text-am-dark leading-relaxed">
						In no event shall Public Code US or its suppliers be liable for any damages (including, without limitation, damages for loss of data or profit, or due to business interruption) arising out of the use or inability to use the materials on Public Code US's website, even if Public Code US or an authorized representative has been notified orally or in writing of the possibility of such damage.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="border-4 border-am-dark bg-am-white p-6">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-am-dark mb-4">6. Accuracy of Materials</h2>
					<p class="font-bold text-am-dark">
						The materials appearing on Public Code US's website could include technical, typographical, or photographic errors. Public Code US does not warrant that any of the materials on our website are accurate, complete, or current. Public Code US may make changes to the materials contained on our website at any time without notice.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-am-dark mb-4">7. Links</h2>
